.SH NAME
xvip_set_format_size \- Set the media bus frame format size
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xvip_set_format_size
.BI "(struct v4l2_mbus_framefmt *format "  ","
.BI "const struct v4l2_subdev_format *fmt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "format" 12
V4L2 frame format on media bus
.IP "fmt" 12
media bus format
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the media bus frame format size. The width / height from the subdevice
format are set to the given media bus format. The new format size is stored
in \fIformat\fP. The width and height are clamped using default min / max values.
